<p>Open the Creative Cloud app, click the â€¢â€¢â€¢ button to the right of the
desired app, and choose Other Versions from the pop-up menu.</p>

<p><img alt="Blog Photo" src="https://grovetech.co/assets/img/blog/2020/20200803Ho/Creative-Cloud-app.png" class="img-fluid rounded m-2" width="700" /></p>

<p>In the list that appears, find the older version you want to
installâ€”likely the version that the rest of the team is usingâ€”and
click Install. Creative Cloud warns you that the app will have its
